"(1) (i) A dense, overcast morning in central cast a gray pall over the A90 as traffic crawled through the mist. The distant hum of engines and the sharp tang of rain filled the air, masking the tension that had begun to settle over the town.\n(2) (i) Near the old Forth Bridge interchange, workers in bright vests moved quickly along the concrete parapets, their radios crackling with urgent updates about recent repairs. The sky was heavy, and the wind seemed to press down on the steel girders and glass office windows lining the road.\n(3) (i) Suddenly, a low rumble vibrated through the ground, followed by a deafening roar from above. Cars in the adjacent lane jerked to a halt as a section of the north span shuddered, then gave way without warning, sending debris tumbling toward the oncoming traffic.\n(4) (i) The incident occurred at precisely 10:17 AM on , as witnessed by several onlookers including , who was standing just south of the collapse zone on the shoulder of the motorway in . Scotland. September 13, 2025.\n(5) (i) The bridge's eastern support columns buckled, spilling concrete chunks and twisted rebar into the air.\n(6) The shockwave of the collapse sent a shudder through the ground, and the air was instantly thick with the acrid scent of burning metal and the shriek of metal on asphalt.\n(7) (i) , standing with his back to the approaching traffic, saw the first support beam snap with a thunderous crack. witnessed a bridge collapse.\n(8) He turned just in time to see a section of the bridge collapse inward, blocking the road and showering the nearby foliage with dust and splinter. Noah Williams."